   "description": "Axel Robert Sture Brunnström was a Swedish Major who was born in Välinge, Malmöhus in 1899. He was the first son of landowner Sture B. and Alice Gravenhorst-Lövenstierne. Axel attended Lundberg's School and Karlberg and received a degree in agriculture from Alnarp. He became a livestock consultant and traveled to Germany, Switzerland, and the United States. He served in the Scania Hussar Regiment and Halland Regiment. Axel was a farmer and served on several committees including the Välinge municipal meeting, municipal council, school board, welfare committee, Art Club, Kulla Equestrian Association, Halmstad Aviation Club's gliding section, Anglo-Swedish Society in Halmstad, and Halland Field Riding Club. He wrote several articles on agriculture and enjoyed hunting, fly fishing, horseback riding, and gliding. Axel received several awards including the Order of the Sword, the Royal Swedish Aero Club's Gold Medal, the Royal Order of Dannebrog, and the Danish Freedom Medal."
